SEMDL Help Topic: reference merge

Usage:
- `ssd merge <input.ssd> --stdout`
- `ssd merge <input.ssd>`

Status:
- `--stdout` returns the merged inline view of `.ssd` with an optional paired `.ssm`.
- Bare `ssd merge <input.ssd>` currently applies only when a paired `.ssm` exists, then removes that sidecar after writing inline output.

Related help:
- `ssd help grammar`
- `ssd help samples`

Sample:
- `ssd merge docs/examples/minimal.ssd --stdout`
